e":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a middleware or route handler throws an error the server needs to know how to handle this. If the server does not know how to handle the error then the only thing it can return to the client is a status code of 500 (Internal Server Error). This is not overly informative.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"HTTPError","type":"heading","anchor":"HTTPError"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hummingbird uses the Error object "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/Hummingbird\/HTTPError","isActive":true},{"text":" throughout its codebase. The server recognises this and can generate a more informative response for the client from it. The error includes the status code that should be returned and a response message if needed. For example","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["router.get(\"user\") { request, context -> User in","    guard let userId = request.uri.queryParameters.get(\"id\", as: Int.self) else {","        throw HTTPError(.badRequest, message: \"Invalid user id\")","    }","    ...","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"HTTPError","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" generated here will be recognised by the server and it will generate a status code 400 (Bad Request) with the body “Invalid user id”."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"HTTPResponseError","text":"HTTPResponseError"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The server knows how to respond to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HTTPError"},{"text":" because it conforms to protocol ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/Hummingbird\/HTTPResponseError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". You can create your own ","type":"text"},{"code":"Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object and conform it to "},{"type":"codeVoice"